  "prompt": "Will I be arrested reentering the US with a bench warrant?",
  "response": "Reentering the U.S. with an active bench warrant can lead to your arrest at the port of entry. A bench warrant is typically issued by a court when someone fails to appear for a scheduled court date or violates a court order. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) officers have access to law enforcement databases and can see active warrants when you reenter the country.\n\nHere\u2019s what could happen:\n\n1. **Detection of the Warrant**: If the bench warrant is active, CBP officers may detain you upon reentry.\n2. **Arrest and Processing**: You could be arrested and turned over to local law enforcement or the jurisdiction that issued the warrant.\n3. **Resolution in Court**: You would need to appear before the court that issued the warrant to address the underlying issue.\n\n### What You Should Do:\n- **Consult an Attorney**: If you know you have a bench warrant, contact a criminal defense attorney before attempting to reenter the U.S. They can help you resolve the warrant proactively.\n- **Address the Warrant**: Work with your attorney to address the warrant, which may involve appearing in court or negotiating a resolution.\n\nIgnoring a bench warrant can lead to more serious consequences, including additional charges or penalties. It\u2019s best to handle it before attempting to reenter the country.",
